    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 13, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Her Majesty’s government have been informed that
                    the British brigs Volante, of Jersey, and Dashing Wave, of Liverpool, have been
                    captured by United States cruisers at Matamoras; and her Majesty’s government
                    have directed me to inquire of you on what grounds these vessels, which are
                    stated to have been engaged in a legitimate trade between the United Kingdom and
                    the Mexican port of Matamoras have been thus captured.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most obedient,
                    humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
